CatDescriptText: Mrs. Lester Williams, 2515 Centre Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 31, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Who is your ward chairman? Does he have any power?  Does he exert it?" answer reads: "I don't know who the ward chairman is and frankly I'm not too interested in politics.  I really don't have the time."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Lester Williams, wearing a light colored satin top with overlapping detail and button, dark belt, and light colored figural patterned skirt, standing in interior with light colored walls
